# Virtual Machine (VM) Set-up Guide

## Prerequisites to this guide

- User has a running VM
- SSH key is connected to Github account
- Repository has been cloned

## Initial VM Set-up

Run init.sh using the following command in the VM terminal:
  - bash scripts/init.sh

This makes the VM up to date with package versions, grants ability to use makefiles,
allows creation of python virtual environments, and installs a useful tool for 
listing files in tree form.

To test, run the 'tree' command. If everything has installed correctly, it should 
run without errors.

## Configure Git Credentials

Run init_git_creds.sh with the following command in the VM terminal:
  - bash scripts.init_git_creds.sh

Expected output should be:

  user.email=<your email>
  user.name=<your github username>

## Create Python Virtual Environment

In the root of the repository, run the 'make update' command.

This creates a virual environment, upgrades pip, and installs needed packages in the 
requirements.txt file.

To activate the environment, run the following command in the VM terminal:
  - . env/bin/activate

Verify the proper packages have been installed by running the 'pip list' command.


